increases in accounts receivable, payments of tax liabilities, expansion and development needs, purchases of shares of
our common stock, as well as purchases of capital assets, equipment and properties, through at least the next 12
months. Based on our current plans, at this time we estimate that capital expenditures (exclusive of common stock
repurchases) are likely to be approximately $100.0 million through December 31, 2019. However, future business
opportunities may cause a change in this estimate.
 
