In May 2014, the FASB issued ASU No. 2014-09, “Revenue from Contracts with Customers (Topic 606)”,
which superseded previous revenue recognition guidance. ASU No. 2014-09 and its amendments were included in
Accounting Standards Codification (“ASC”) 606, “Revenue from Contracts with Customers”. ASC 606 requires that a
company recognizes revenue at an amount that reflects the consideration to which the company expects to be entitled in
exchange for transferring goods or services to a customer. The Company adopted ASC 606 effective January 1, 2018,
using the modified retrospective approach, with no impact to the opening retained earnings. Results for periods
beginning on or after January 1, 2018 are presented under ASC 606, while prior periods are not adjusted and continue
to be reported in accordance with the prior accounting guidance under ASC 605, “Revenue Recognition”. See Note 2.
 
