Restricted Stock Units
 
Stock-based compensation cost for restricted stock units is measured based on the closing fair market value of
the Company’s common stock at the date of grant. In the event that the Company has the option and intent to settle a
restricted stock unit in cash, the award is classified as a liability and revalued at each balance sheet date.
 
